          <h3 style="text-align:center;">What an Annual Service Protects</h3>
          <ul class="pf-check-list">
            <li>Carbon monoxide safety. Back boilers and older open-flue boilers in WA10 carry a higher CO risk than modern sealed-flue combis. Annual combustion testing and spillage testing is the only reliable way to confirm your boiler is not exposing your household to CO</li>
            <li>Manufacturer warranty maintained. Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal and Baxi require annual servicing by a Gas Safe engineer and an updated Benchmark record. Missing a year voids the warranty entirely — regardless of boiler age</li>
            <li>Lower gas bills. A serviced boiler runs up to 10 to 15% more efficiently. In St Helens properties where many boilers are older models already operating below peak efficiency, annual servicing has a meaningful impact on gas bills</li>
            <li>Early fault detection before the winter breakdown. In older WA10 and WA11 properties, worn components are more common. Identifying a failing thermocouple in October costs far less than an emergency call-out in December</li>
            <li>Inhibitor levels maintained. Corrosion inhibitor degrades annually. Every service includes a test and top-up to the correct concentration level</li>
            <li>Legal compliance for St Helens landlords. Annual gas safety inspection is a legal requirement. The CP12 must cover all gas appliances. See <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HSE landlord gas safety obligations</a></li>
            <li>Annual reminder included. We add you to our reminder list after your first service and contact you when the next is due</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
