        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue gas analysis</strong><p>Combustion gases tested to confirm correct and safe burning. Critical for back boilers and older boilers common across WA10.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Combustion spillage test</strong><p>For back boilers and open-flue appliances, a spillage test is carried out to confirm combustion products are exiting via the flue and not spilling into the room. A legally required check for all open-flue appliances.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas pressure and flow rate</strong><p>Gas supply pressure and flow rate confirmed correct. Low pressure causes lockouts and poor performance across all boiler types.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Burner and heat exchanger</strong><p>Burner removed and inspected. Heat exchanger checked for corrosion and cracking. Back boiler heat exchangers in confined spaces require particular attention.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue baffle and draught diverter</strong><p>Specific to back boilers and open-flue boilers. Flue baffle checked for correct positioning. Draught diverter tested to confirm it opens correctly under operating conditions.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue integrity and ventilation</strong><p>Full flue route inspected. Ventilation in the room checked to confirm adequate air for combustion. Open-flue appliances require permanent ventilation that is often blocked by residents.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Safety devices tested</strong><p>Pressure relief valve, overheat thermostat and gas valve all tested for correct operation under fault conditions.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Inhibitor level tested and topped up</strong><p>Inhibitor concentration tested. Low inhibitor accelerates corrosion and sludge. Topped up to the correct level on every service — never skipped.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Controls and programmer</strong><p>Thermostat, programmer and any zone valves checked for correct operation. A faulty control component causes uneven heating even with a fully functional boiler.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Full function test and Benchmark updated</strong><p>Full heating and hot water cycle run. Benchmark record updated with service date and findings. Certificate emailed same day. This step protects your manufacturer warranty.</p></div></div>
