        <h3 style="text-align:center;">Combined Service and Gas Safety Certificate. £175. Including Gas Fires.</h3>
        <p>St Helens landlords are legally required under the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safety Regulations 1998</a> to have all gas appliances including boilers and gas fires serviced and inspected annually by a Gas Safe registered engineer and to hold a valid CP12 gas safety certificate. A copy must be provided to tenants within 28 days of issue.</p>
        <p>Our combined visit covers the full boiler service, the CP12 inspection and checks on any gas fires in the property in one appointment at £175. For WA10 properties with both a back boiler and a gas fire, this single visit satisfies all requirements. Both documents emailed the same day. Accepted by all St Helens letting agents and the <a href="https://www.nrla.org.uk/resources/gas-safety" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NRLA</a>. We service portfolio landlords across all St Helens WA postcodes and can coordinate tenant access.</p>
