  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Signs Your St Helens Boiler Needs Servicing Now</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Do not wait for the annual reminder if your boiler is showing any of these signs. We can often attend the same day.</p>
      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Gas fire or back boiler with a lazy, yellow or orange flame</strong><p>A healthy gas flame is blue. Yellow or orange on a back boiler or gas fire indicates incomplete combustion. This is particularly dangerous in enclosed living room settings where combustion products can accumulate. Stop using the appliance immediately. Call us or Cadent Gas on 0800 111 999 if you suspect a gas emergency.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler making unusual noises</strong><p>Banging, kettling, gurgling or whistling sounds indicate developing faults. In older WA10 boilers, these often indicate scale build-up or a failing component that is far cheaper to address at a service than after a full breakdown.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler locking out repeatedly</strong><p>A boiler shutting itself down repeatedly is detecting a fault. Error codes point to the cause. A diagnostic visit identifies the underlying issue before it causes a complete failure during winter.</p></div></div>
